OL,3,CMouldy food and rats: Children face
OL,4,C'almost-Dickensian' levels of poverty
OL,6,FSome young people in England are
OL,7,Fliving in an "almost-Dickensian level
OL,8,Fof poverty" and it's a crisis that
OL,9,Fcan't be ignored, the Children's
OL,10,FCommissioner said, as she insisted the
OL,11,Ftwo-child benefit limit must be
OL,12,Fscrapped.
OL,14,FChildren spoke of food packages that
OL,15,Fwere mouldy and out of date, rats
OL,16,Fbiting through the walls and black
OL,17,Fmould making them ill, in a new report
OL,18,Fpublished on Tuesday which reveals the
OL,19,F"real hardship" facing some families.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
