OL,3,CMouldy food and rats: Children face
OL,4,C'almost-Dickensian' levels of poverty
OL,6,FOne child spoke of receiving mouldy
OL,7,Ffood packages, saying "I know I'm poor
OL,8,Fbut I'm not going to eat mouldy food."
OL,10,FAnother spoke of a mould problem that
OL,11,F"was making me so ill", but it was not
OL,12,Fproperly fixed by the council, leaving
OL,13,F"a hole in our floor."
OL,15,FDame Rachel de Souza said that
OL,16,F"children shared harrowing accounts of
OL,17,Fhardship, with some in almost-
OL,18,FDickensian levels of poverty".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
