OL,3,CMouldy food and rats: Children face
OL,4,C'almost-Dickensian' levels of poverty
OL,6,F"They don't talk about 'poverty' as an
OL,7,Fabstract concept but about not having
OL,8,Fthe things that most people would
OL,9,Fconsider basic: a safe home that isn't
OL,10,Fmouldy or full or rats, with a bed big
OL,11,Fenough to stretch out in, 'luxury'
OL,12,Ffood like bacon, a place to do
OL,13,Fhomework, heating, privacy in the
OL,14,Fbathroom and being able to wash,
OL,15,Fhaving their friends over, and not
OL,16,Fhaving to travel hours to school," she
OL,17,Fsaid.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
